title.narrative: 6.1. By 2021, government and partners have in place an integrated child and family welfare system to prevent and respond toviolence, abuse, exploitation and neglect.

description.narrative: A national statutory case management system for addressing violence and vulnerability has reached13,294children.There is no national information management system to accompany it as yet.Theharmonisedsocial welfarecommunity-based case management reached15,308children. A national campaign for familycare had an estimated 2million population coverage and 18,170 persons were reached with direct social behaviour engagement.There has been a 20.8 per cent increase of children in institutional care and Government has raised concerns over increases in teen pregnancy and gender-based violence during lockdowns. The new Government publicly committed to adopting the Children’s Code Bill and addressing violence against children. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:07/01/2022
